Motives for such a thing can be elusive and enigmatic.<br><br>
Convolutions of facts, of the truth, often stem from delusions, distortions of reality, or just plain pathological lying. I am in the same quandry as you. Why?<br><br>
As a Vietnam Veteran, and someone who has repressed lots of not so nice things, the last thing I would do would be to *make up* a story with as devastating a connection as that. Children are the absolute victims of war, and suffer horribly. They never ask to be in such a situation. They are catapulted into the maelstrom by the frenzy of their adult keepers without the skills or emptional strength to survive, and are damaged for life. The absolute horror is when children are made instruments of war by obeying their elders and *deliver* hand grenades to unsuspecting soldiers. The middle east is famous for that strategy. Children used as weapons in the Vietnam War were sparse but not uncommon.<br><br>
If we delve too deeply into this, I fear we will know less than we know now. The twists and turns of the mind of the person who made the claim will probably never be truly known.   
